<title>USA: IBM increases repurchase plan by $3.5 billion.</title>
<headline>IBM increases repurchase plan by $3.5 billion.</headline>
<dateline>ARMONK, N.Y.</dateline>
<text>
<p>International Business Machines Corp. said Tuesday its board has authorised the repurchase of up to an additional $3.5 billion of common shares.</p>
<p>The Armonk, N.Y.-based computer giant said it plans to buy shares on the open market from time to time, depending on market conditions.</p>
<p>Since Jan. 31, 1995, IBM has repurchased more than $9.7 billion of common stock under a series of buyback authorisations, it said.</p>
<p>IBM's stock, which has risen sharply recently, edged down 12.5 cents to $157.75 on the New York Stock exchange at midday.</p>
